  "prompt": "What are G4 nations?",
  "response": "The G4 nations refer to a group of four countries\u2014India, Brazil, Germany, and Japan\u2014that support each other's bids for permanent seats on the United Nations Security Council (UNSC). These nations aim to reform the UNSC to better reflect the current geopolitical landscape and ensure greater representation from regions like Africa, Latin America, and Asia. The G4 nations believe that expanding the permanent membership of the UNSC would enhance its legitimacy, effectiveness, and responsiveness to global challenges.",
